This paper belongs to the field of information retrieval (cs.IR) as it focuses on gathering and analyzing data related to display advertising on the web. The paper also involves the use of crawling and data mining techniques, which are commonly used in the sub-field of information retrieval. 

Additionally, the paper may also fall under the sub-category of social and information networks (cs.SI) as it involves analyzing the behavior of users and advertisers on web sites. 

The paper may also be relevant to the sub-field of computational linguistics (cs.CL) as it involves analyzing the content of display ads and landing pages. 

The sub-category of cyber security (cs.CY) may also be relevant as the paper discusses the impact of user profiles and cookies on the ads that are shown. 

Finally, the sub-category of cryptography and security (cs.CR) may also be relevant as the paper involves the collection and analysis of potentially sensitive data related to user behavior and advertising practices.
